        <h2>How to Create an AI Hug Video</h2>

        <h3>Step 1: Upload Your Photo</h3>
        <p>
          Start by uploading a clear portrait photo. For the best result, use an
          image with good lighting, a visible face, and a clean background.
        </p>

        <h3>Step 2: Choose the Hug Video Style</h3>
        <p>
          Select a realistic, cinematic, romantic, family, or social-media-ready
          hug style. Different styles can create different emotions and visual
          effects.
        </p>

        <h3>Step 3: Generate the Video</h3>
        <p>
          Click the generate button and let the AI create the animation. The
          system will analyze the image and produce a short AI-generated hug
          video.
        </p>

        <h3>Step 4: Preview the Result</h3>
        <p>
          Watch the generated video carefully. Check the motion, face
          consistency, lighting, and overall feeling before downloading.
        </p>

        <h3>Step 5: Download and Share</h3>
        <p>
          Download the final video and share it on TikTok, Instagram Reels,
          YouTube Shorts, Telegram, or other social platforms.
        </p>

        <h2>Best Practices</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Use a high-resolution photo.</li>
          <li>Avoid blurry or heavily filtered images.</li>
          <li>Choose photos with natural lighting.</li>
          <li>Keep the subject clear and centered.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>FAQ</h2>

        <h3>Can I create an AI hug video from one photo?</h3>
        <p>
          Yes. Many AI video tools can generate short animations from a single
          image.
        </p>

        <h3>Is this suitable for TikTok or Reels?</h3>
        <p>
          Yes. AI hug videos are often used for short-form emotional content,
          social media storytelling, and creative video posts.
        </p>

        <h3>What image works best?</h3>
        <p>
          A clear, front-facing image with good lighting usually produces better
          results.
        </p>
